4 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 50-11.1-23 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 50-11.1-23. Eligibility for best in class program.
7 1. An approved four-year old program, federally funded head start program, or early
8 childhood program may submit, in the form and manner prescribed by the department,
9 an application to the department under section 50-11.1-22, if the provider certifies to
10 the department the provider:
11 a. Operates an approved four-year old program, federally funded head start
12 program, or early childhood program in this state;
13 b. Operates a program for children who have reached four years of age before
14 August first in the year of enrollment , unless otherwise provided in subdivision d
15 of subsection 1 of section 50 - 11.1 - 21 ;
16 c. Operates a program that has a duration of at least four hundred hours over a
17 period of at least thirty-two consecutive weeks;
18 d. Incorporates within the program at least ten hours of research-based family
19 engagement;
20 e. Has been determined to meet the standards and expectations of no less than
21 step three in the North Dakota early childhood quality improvement system; has
22 met the standards and expectations of a nationally recognized early childhood
23 accrediting entity; has met the federal performance standards for head start; or
24 has obtained approval or certification from the department of public instruction;
25 f. Admits children of all learning abilities;
26 g. Admits children who receive assistance from the child care assistance program;
27 and
28 h. Operates in compliance with the program requirements, including:
29 (1) Complying with requirements related to qualifications, training, and
30 professional development of staff delivering services in the best in class
31 program; and
